'''Sci-Hub'''是一個[[影子圖書館|影子圖書館]]。它利用不同方法繞過出版商的[[付費牆|付費牆]]<ref name="eLife"/><ref name="BohannonBio">{{cite journal|last1=Bohannon|first1=John|date=2016-04-28|title=The frustrated science student behind Sci-Hub|url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2016/04/frustrated-science-student-behind-sci-hub?IntCmp=scihub-1-11|url-status=live|journal=Science|language=en| volume=352| issue=6285|pages=511|bibcode=2016Sci...352..511B|doi=10.1126/science.352.6285.511|pmid=27126021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181027233538/https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2016/04/frustrated-science-student-behind-sci-hub?IntCmp=scihub-1-11|archive-date=2018-10-27|access-date=2018-10-27}}</ref><ref name=Elbakyan2017>{{cite news|access-date=2018-04-30|title=Some facts on Sci-Hub that Wikipedia gets wrong|url=https://engineuring.wordpress.com/2017/07/02/some-facts-on-sci-hub-that-wikipedia-gets-wrong/|date=2017-07-02|author=Alexandra Elbakyan|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203192037/https://engineuring.wordpress.com/2017/07/02/some-facts-on-sci-hub-that-wikipedia-gets-wrong/|archive-date=2017-12-03|url-status=live|author-link=Alexandra Elbakyan}}</ref>，以[[盗版|不考慮版权问题]]的方式提供数以百万计的[[学术出版|學術論文]]和著作<ref name="eLife"/>。2011年，[[哈薩克|哈薩克]]研究生[[亞歷珊卓·艾爾巴金|亞歷珊卓·艾爾巴金]]因為擋在[[付費牆|付費牆]]背後的研究論文成本過高，而決定成立Sci-Hub。它的使用者遍佈世界各地<ref name="eLife" /><ref name=Bohannon>{{cite journal |last1=Bohannon|first1=John |title= Who's downloading pirated papers? Everyone |journal= [[科学_(期刊)|Science]] |doi= 10.1126/science.aaf5664 |date=2016-04-28 |volume=352 |number=6285 |pages= 508–512|pmid=27126020 }}</ref>。2019年9月，網站持有人宣稱Sci-Hub每天處理約400,000宗請求<ref name="roskomsvoboda">{{cite web|url=https://roskomsvoboda.org/49416/|title=Sci-Hub отметил восьмилетие|website=Roskomsvoboda.org|date=2019-09-06|access-date=2019-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191021170135/https://roskomsvoboda.org/49416/|archive-date=2019-10-21|url-status=live}}</ref>。2021年2月，Sci-Hub的首頁顯示它儲存了超過8500万篇論文。

Sci-Hub和艾爾巴金在美國兩度被控以侵犯版權。兩次皆因{{link-en|缺席宣判|Default judgment|答辯人缺席}}而敗訴，令Sci-Hub失去了一些互聯網[[域名|域名]]<ref name=Chawla>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/11/court-demands-search-engines-and-internet-service-providers-block-sci-hub|title=Court demands that search engines and internet service providers block Sci-Hub|work=Science {{!}} AAAS|first=Dalmeet Singh|last=Chawla| date=2017-11-06|language=en|access-date=2017-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171123071628/http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/11/court-demands-search-engines-and-internet-service-providers-block-sci-hub|archive-date=2017-11-23|url-status=live}}</ref>。自此它便定期更換域名<ref name="eLife">{{Cite journal|last1=Himmelstein|first1=Daniel S|last2=Romero|first2=Ariel Rodriguez|last3=Levernier|first3=Jacob G|last4=Munro|first4=Thomas Anthony|last5=McLaughlin|first5=Stephen Reid|last6=Greshake Tzovaras|first6=Bastian|last7=Greene|first7=Casey S|date=2018-03-01|title=Sci-Hub provides access to nearly all scholarly literature|journal=eLife|language=en|volume=7|doi=10.7554/eLife.32822|issn=2050-084X|pmc=5832410|pmid=29424689}}</ref>。

Sci-Hub得到[[科學界|科學界]]、学术界、出版界的赞譽<ref name=WaPo>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/this-student-put-50-million-stolen-research-articles-online-and-theyre-free/2016/03/30/7714ffb4-eaf7-11e5-b0fd-073d5930a7b7_story.html|title=This student put 50 million stolen research articles online. And they're free.|date=2016-03-30|website=The Washington Post|last1=Rosenwald|first1=Michael S.|access-date=2018-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414201340/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/this-student-put-50-million-stolen-research-articles-online-and-theyre-free/2016/03/30/7714ffb4-eaf7-11e5-b0fd-073d5930a7b7_story.html|archive-date=2019-04-14|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=":7">{{Cite journal|date=2016-12-22|title=Nature's 10|journal=Nature|volume=540|issue=7634|pages=507–515|doi=10.1038/540507a|pmid=30905952|bibcode=2016Natur.540..507.|doi-access=free}}</ref>
，認為它能有效傳播科學界的知識，把得到政府資助的研究成果免費提供給大眾<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2018/sep/13/scientific-publishing-rip-off-taxpayers-fund-research|title = Scientific publishing is a rip-off. We fund the research – it should be free | George Monbiot|date = 2018-09-13|access-date = 2021-06-23|archive-date = 2018-09-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180913071701/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2018/sep/13/scientific-publishing-rip-off-taxpayers-fund-research|dead-url = no}}</ref>。出版商則批評它侵犯版權<ref name=Bohannon/><ref name=":4">{{Cite web|author=Kravets, David|date=2016-04-03|url=https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/04/a-spiritual-successor-to-aaron-swartz-is-angering-publishers-all-over-again/|title=A spiritual successor to Aaron Swartz is angering publishers all over again|website=arstechnica.com|access-date=2016-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170111180537/http://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/04/a-spiritual-successor-to-aaron-swartz-is-angering-publishers-all-over-again/|archive-date=2017-01-11|url-status=live}}</ref>，令自身收入減少<ref name=shadowill>{{cite journal|url=http://eprints.rclis.org/30981/|authors=Gardner, Gabriel J. and McLaughlin, Stephen R. and Asher, Andrew D.|title=Shadow Libraries and You: Sci-Hub Usage and the Future of ILL|pages=568–587|series=ACRL 2017, Baltimore, Maryland.|date=2017-03-25|type=conference paper|hdl=10760/30981|access-date=2018-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180128193207/http://eprints.rclis.org/30981/|archive-date=2018-01-28|url-status=live}}</ref>，危害大学的[[网络安全|网络安全]]（不過出版商可能只是誇大有關威脅）<ref name="timeshighereducation.com">{{Cite web|date=2020-11-06|title=Sci-Hub 'security risk' claims irk open access advocates|url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/news/sci-hub-security-risk-claims-irk-open-access-advocates|access-date=2020-11-16|website=Times Higher Education (THE)|language=en|archive-date=2021-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211108173836/https://www.timeshighereducation.com/news/sci-hub-security-risk-claims-irk-open-access-advocates|dead-url=no}}</ref>。Sci-Hub亦誘使出版商把付費牆設得更严格<ref name="RussellSanchez">{{cite journal |last1=Russell |first1=Carrie |last2=Sanchez |first2=Ed |title=Sci-Hub unmasked: Piracy, information policy, and your library |journal=College & Research Libraries News |date=2016-03-01 |volume=77 |issue=3 |pages=122–125 |doi=10.5860/crln.77.3.9457 |language=en |issn=2150-6698 |doi-access=free }}</ref>。

艾爾巴金在為Sci-Hub辯護時，會反過來质疑出版商的商業手法是否符合道德和《[[世界人权宣言|世界人权宣言]]》第二十七條<ref name=":5">{{Cite news|last=Van der Sar|first=Ernesto|date=2015-06-27|title=Sci-Hub Tears Down Academia’s “Illegal” Copyright Paywalls|work=TorrentFreak|url=https://torrentfreak.com/sci-hub-tears-down-academias-illegal-copyright-paywalls-150627/|access-date=2021-09-27|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304144853/https://torrentfreak.com/sci-hub-tears-down-academias-illegal-copyright-paywalls-150627/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Newtonew2016>{{Cite web|url=https://newtonew.com/discussions/sci-hub-against-information-inequality|title="Sci-Hub: «победить копирайт и информационное неравенство"|publisher=Newtonew|accessdate=2016-08-13|archive-date=2016-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160609181635/https://newtonew.com/discussions/sci-hub-against-information-inequality|dead-url=no}}</ref>。她堅持營運Sci-Hub是一种[[道德律令|道德律令]]，法律不應阻止她。她曾表示：「如果美国人全都遵從惡法，那麼他們到了今天仍會受女皇統治，奴隸制亦會繼續存在」<ref>Schiermeier, Q. (2020). "Pirate paper website Sci-Hub dealt another blow by US courts." Nature.Schiermeier, Q. (2020). "Pirate paper website Sci-Hub dealt another blow by US courts." Nature.</ref>。

== 歷史 ==
[[File:Scihub_Feb_2016_pop-adjusted.png|thumb]]
Sci-Hub由[[亞歷珊卓·艾爾巴金|亞歷珊卓·艾爾巴金]]建立。1988年，艾爾巴金在[[哈萨克斯坦|哈萨克斯坦]]出生<ref name="BohannonBio">{{cite journal|last1=Bohannon|first1=John|date=2016-04-28|title=The frustrated science student behind Sci-Hub|url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2016/04/frustrated-science-student-behind-sci-hub?IntCmp=scihub-1-11|url-status=live|journal=Science|language=en| volume=352| issue=6285|pages=511|bibcode=2016Sci...352..511B|doi=10.1126/science.352.6285.511|pmid=27126021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181027233538/https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2016/04/frustrated-science-student-behind-sci-hub?IntCmp=scihub-1-11|archive-date=2018-10-27|access-date=2018-10-27}}</ref>。她後來於哈薩克國立科技大學取得電腦科學理學士學位<ref>{{cite web|title=Lifeboat Foundation Bios: Alexandra A. Elbakyan|url=http://lifeboat.com/ex/bios.alexandra.a.elbakyan|publisher=Lifeboat Foundation|access-date=2016-02-15|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100507022228/http://lifeboat.com/ex/bios.alexandra.a.elbakyan|archive-date=2010-05-07}}</ref>。她在大學畢業後，於莫斯科找到一份有關電腦安全的工作<ref name="Bohannon-28-April-2016">{{cite journal|first=John |last=Bohannon|title=The frustrated science student behind Sci-Hub|journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]]|doi=10.1126/science.352.6285.511 |date=2016-04-29|volume=352|page=511|number=6285|bibcode=2016Sci...352..511B |pmid=27126021}}</ref>。2010年，她參與德國[[弗赖堡大学|弗赖堡大学]]一項有關[[脑机接口|脑机接口]]的研究項目<ref name="Labio">{{cite news|url=http://labiotech.eu/this-27-years-old-woman-is-shaking-the-scientific-publishing-industry/ |first=Denise Neves |last=Gameiro |date=2016-06-04 |title=This 27-year-old Woman is Shaking up the Scientific Publishing Industry |work=Labiotech.eu |quote=Alexandra Elbakyan, a 27-year-old researcher from Kazakhstan...was studying ‘Neuroscience and Consciousness' in labs at Georgia Tech (US) and University of Freiburg (Germany)...she was forced to pirate papers for herself and other researchers |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170111181359/http://labiotech.eu/this-27-years-old-woman-is-shaking-the-scientific-publishing-industry/ |archive-date=2017-01-11 |url-status=dead }}</ref>，對[[超人类主义|超人類主義]]思想產生興趣。同年參加[[佐治亚理工学院|佐治亞理工學院]]的夏季交流項目<ref>{{cite news|url=http://pwp.gatech.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/516/2016/10/PotterGroup.html |title=People |publisher=[[Georgia_Institute_of_Technology|Georgia Institute of Technology]] |quote=Alexandra Elbakyan [...] Summer 2010 [...] Programming and data analysis |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170111210530/http://pwp.gatech.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/516/2016/10/PotterGroup.html |archive-date=2017-01-11 |url-status=dead }}</ref>。

她於2011年回到哈薩克斯坦，在當地大學展開研究。艾爾巴金表示，她當時難以取得需要用到的科學論文，於是便開始在互聯網上尋找各種繞過付費牆的方法。她之後繼續以那些方法獲取論文，在[[网络论坛|网络论坛]]上分享給有需要者。同年她著手開發Sci-Hub，把上述過程自動化<ref name=":5"/><ref name="torrentfreak.com">{{Cite web|last=Van der Sar|first=Ernesto|date=2015-09-16|title=Science "Pirate" Attacks Elsevier's Copyright Monopoly in Court - TorrentFreak|url=https://torrentfreak.com/science-pirate-attacks-elseviers-copyright-monopoly-in-court-150916/|url-status=no|website=TorrentFreak|accessdate=2015-10-05|archive-date=2021-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211118022912/https://torrentfreak.com/science-pirate-attacks-elseviers-copyright-monopoly-in-court-150916/}}</ref>。2011年9月5日，Sci-Hub正式上線<ref name=":8">{{Cite news|last=Maxwell|first=Andy|date=2021-09-06|title=Sci-Hub Celebrates 10 Year Anniversary By Uploading 2.3m New Articles|work=TorrentFreak|url=https://torrentfreak.com/sci-hub-celebrates-10-year-anniversary-by-uploading-2-3m-new-articles-210905/|access-date=2021-09-27|archive-date=2021-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211124184711/https://torrentfreak.com/sci-hub-celebrates-10-year-anniversary-by-uploading-2-3m-new-articles-210905/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2013年開始，Sci-Hub在印度、印度尼西亞、巴基斯坦、伊朗、中華人民共和國、巴西等開發中國家逐漸盛行。其中在最初網站的創建目標中，艾爾巴金便明確地提到將為資源較少的機構與國家提供研究資料。而在2014年，學術界開始預測網站將會發展為類似 [[Napster|Napster]]的服務<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Is Biblioleaks inevitable?|author=Adam G. Dunn、Enrico Coiera和Kenneth D. Mandl|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24755534|journal=《{{Link-en|醫學網際網路|Journal of Medical Internet Research}}》|issue=第4期|doi=10.2196/jmir.3331|others=|year=2014年4月22日|volume=第16卷|page=E112頁|pmid=24755534|access-date=2016年3月8日|archive-date=2016年9月21日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921155302/http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24755534|dead-url=no}}</ref>。該計畫的原始[[網域名稱|網域名稱]]為<code>Sci-Hub.org</code>，在被美國法院禁封前平均每天有80,000多名訪客瀏覽。

2017年，宾夕法尼亚大学的Daniel Himmelstein研究了Sci-Hub，发现网站上的论文共有81,600,000篇，包含了所有学术论文的69%，基本能满足大部分的论文需求，因为剩下的31%是研究者不想获取的论文。<ref>{{cite news|author1=Dirk|title=时隔一年，Science再发文: Sci-Hub盗版论文量巨大 订阅式期刊注定失败|url=http://www.cailiaoniu.com/93695.html|accessdate=2018-02-22|date=2017-07-28|archive-date=2018-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180222104834/http://www.cailiaoniu.com/93695.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2021年9月，该网站為庆祝成立十週年，而向数据库上传超过230万篇文章<ref name="motherboard"></ref><ref name=":8" />。

== 網站運作 ==
Sci-Hub依靠用戶捐款來維持運作<ref name=Bohannon/>。艾爾巴金避免第三方人士參與網站營運，從而加強它的安全性。它的[[PHP|PHP]]代碼由她親手撰寫；除此之外，她亦亲自架設Sci-hub的伺服器，自行負責日常維護工作<ref>{{cite web |last1=Alexandra |first1=Elbakyan |title=Sci-Hub and Alexandra basic information |url=https://engineuring.wordpress.com/2019/03/31/sci-hub-and-alexandra-basic-information/ |website=engineuring |date=2019-03-30 |access-date=2020-09-20 |archive-date=2021-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211006212207/https://engineuring.wordpress.com/2019/03/31/sci-hub-and-alexandra-basic-information/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。部分司法機關曾下令有關機構須沒收Sci-Hub的域名。為了繼續營運，它只好更換其他URL地址和IP地址<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/616677/the-website-that-offered-47-million-pirated-academic-papers-is-back/|title=The website that offered 47 million pirated academic papers is back|date=2016-02-14|access-date=2020-10-20|website=[[石英财经网|Quartz]]|last=Sonnad|first=Nikhil|archive-date=2021-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211006173101/https://qz.com/616677/the-website-that-offered-47-million-pirated-academic-papers-is-back/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===文章來源===
Sci-Hub憑着外流的身份驗證資訊，去獲得擋在付費牆背後的學術論文<ref name="eLife"/><ref name=RussellSanchez/>。至於該些身份驗證資訊從何而來則沒有清晰答案<ref name="WaPo" />。它們有些可能被原擁有者賣掉<ref name="IGS">{{cite news |last1=Graber-Stiehl |first1=Ian |title=Science's Pirate Queen |url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/2/8/16985666/alexandra-elbakyan-sci-hub-open-access-science-papers-lawsuit |work=The Verge |date=2018-02-08 |access-date=2018-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028163915/https://www.theverge.com/2018/2/8/16985666/alexandra-elbakyan-sci-hub-open-access-science-papers-lawsuit |archive-date=2018-10-28 |url-status=live }}</ref>，有些則可能經[[钓鱼式攻击|钓鱼式攻击]]取得<ref name="Ruff">{{cite news|url=https://www.chronicle.com/article/Librarians-Find-Themselves/235353|title=Librarians Find Themselves Caught Between Journal Pirates and Publishers|last1=Ruff|first1=Corinne|date=2016-02-18|work=The Chronicle of Higher Education|access-date=2018-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028225820/https://www.chronicle.com/article/Librarians-Find-Themselves/235353|archive-date=2018-10-28|url-status=live}}.</ref><ref name="RussellSanchez"/>。艾爾巴金否認自己發過钓鱼郵件，並表示：「我並不在乎該些密碼的出處」<ref name="WaPo" />。艾爾巴金在2021年提到：「該些身份驗證資訊由學生、教職人員、學術機構自願提供，因此我並沒有必要破壞互聯網安全」<ref name="Okere, K 2021"/><ref>Hoy, M. B. (2017). "Sci-Hub: What Librarians Should Know and Do about Article Piracy." Medical Reference Services Quarterly 36(1): 73-78</ref>。根據{{link-en|学術出版協会|Society for Scholarly Publishing}}的說法（它的部分成員曾控告Sci-Hub），Sci-Hub所使用的身份驗證資訊能夠存取大學網絡上的其他資訊，當中部分更於黑市出現<ref name="SK">{{cite news |last1=Pitts |first1=Andrew |title=Guest Post: Think Sci-Hub is Just Downloading PDFs? Think Again – The Scholarly Kitchen |url=https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2018/09/18/guest-post-think-sci-hub-is-just-downloading-pdfs-think-again/ |work=The Scholarly Kitchen |date=2018-09-18 |access-date=2018-10-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028230037/https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2018/09/18/guest-post-think-sci-hub-is-just-downloading-pdfs-think-again/ |archive-date=2018-10-28 |url-status=live }}</ref>。數篇報導寫道，Sci-Hub滲透了超過370間大學的電腦網絡，橫跨39個國家。若把每個國家分開來看，那麽美國就有超過150間學術機構被滲透；加拿大有超過30間；英國有超過39間；瑞典則有超過10間<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/1773765/sci-hub-creator-says-shes-not-working-for-russian-intelligence/|title=The "Robin Hood of science" says she's not a Russian asset|first=Justin|last=Rohrlich|website=Quartz|access-date=2021-12-22|archive-date=2020-07-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200725021403/https://qz.com/1773765/sci-hub-creator-says-shes-not-working-for-russian-intelligence/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dn.se/ekonomi/spion-eller-en-kunskapens-robin-hood/?site=mobile|title=Spion eller en kunskapens Robin Hood?|date=2020-01-10|newspaper=Dagens Nyheter|accessdate=2021-06-23|archive-date=2021-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211223111841/https://www.dn.se/ekonomi/spion-eller-en-kunskapens-robin-hood/?site=mobile|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/russian-pirate-hacked-39-british-universities-6x9335xh9|title=Russian pirate hacked 39 British universities|first=Danny|last=Fortson|via=www.thetimes.co.uk|accessdate=2021-06-23|archive-date=2021-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211030030648/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/russian-pirate-hacked-39-british-universities-6x9335xh9|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tricitynews.com/news/ubc-sfu-allegedly-hacked-by-russian-intelligence-backed-internet-pirates-1.24042570|title=UBC, SFU allegedly hacked by Russian intelligence-backed internet pirates|first=Stefan|last=Labbé|website=Tri-City News|access-date=2021-06-23|archive-date=2020-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130110055/https://www.tricitynews.com/news/ubc-sfu-allegedly-hacked-by-russian-intelligence-backed-internet-pirates-1.24042570|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===傳送機制===
Sci-Hub收錄了差不多所有[[学术出版|学术出版商]]出版的文章，像是愛思唯爾、施普林格·自然、[[电气电子工程师学会|电气电子工程师学会]]、[[美国化学学会|美国化学学会]]、威立-布莱克威尔、[[英国皇家化学学会|英国皇家化学学会]]。它亦收錄以開放取用形式授權的作品。它向用戶提供有關內容時不會考慮出版商的版權<ref name=Bohannon/>，亦不要求用戶訂閱或付費<ref name=":3">{{cite journal |last1=Cabanac |first1=Guillaume |title=Bibliogifts in LibGen? A study of a text-sharing platform driven by biblioleaks and crowdsourcing |journal=Journal of the Association for Information Science and Technology |date=2016 |volume=67 |issue=4 |pages=874–884 |doi=10.1002/asi.23445 |url=http://www.irit.fr/publis/SIG/2015_JASIST_C.pdf |access-date=2016-08-25 |citeseerx=10.1.1.698.4283 |s2cid=6643023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310035801/https://www.irit.fr/publis/SIG/2015_JASIST_C.pdf |archive-date=2016-03-10 |url-status=live }}</ref>{{rp|10}}。

用戶能以不同方式獲取文章，可行方法有於Sci-Hub的搜索栏或網址輸入[[DOI|DOI]]、於出版商的域名前方加入Sci-Hub的域名<ref>{{cite news |last1=Heathers |first1=James |title=Why Sci-Hub Will Win |url=https://medium.com/@jamesheathers/why-sci-hub-will-win-595b53aae9fa |work=James Heathers via Medium |date=2016-05-02 |access-date=2018-04-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180429024908/https://medium.com/@jamesheathers/why-sci-hub-will-win-595b53aae9fa |archive-date=2018-04-29 |url-status=live }}</ref>。Sci-Hub會把一些[[开放获取|金色開放取用]]作品的元數據跟CrossRef和Unpaywall比對，然後把請求重新導向至其他網站。它有時亦會要求用戶輸入[[验证码|验证码]]<ref name=SKhow/>。用戶還可透過[[即時通訊|即時通訊]]服務[[Telegram|Telegram]]的機械人獲取文章<ref>{{cite news|title=Sci-Hub Offers Encrypted Bot to Help Users Stay Safe – Deep Dot Web|url=https://www.deepdotweb.com/2016/05/23/sci-hub-offers-encrypted-bot-help-users-stay-safe/|date=2016-05-16|author=American Guerrilla|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181118182646/https://www.deepdotweb.com/2016/05/23/sci-hub-offers-encrypted-bot-help-users-stay-safe/|archive-date=2018-11-18|url-status=dead}}</ref>。

如果Sci-Hub發現所請求的論文已存放伺服器當中，那麽便會立即回應請求。若在伺服器找不到該論文，那麽就會向用戶顯示一個等待畫面，同時後台會向一系列[[代理服务器|代理服务器]]給出其他人的证书，直到找到該論文為止。之後再把它儲存在伺服器中，同時回應請求<ref name="eLife"/><ref name=Ruff/><ref name="ALM">{{Cite web|last=Banks|first=Marcus|url=https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|title=Sci-Hub: What It Is and Why It Matters|date=2016-05-31|website=American Libraries|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918042400/https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|archive-date=2016-09-18|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=SKhow>{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=David |title=Sci-Hub: How Does it Work? |url=https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2016/02/25/sci-hub-how-does-it-work |work=The Scholarly Kitchen |date=2016-02-25 |access-date=2018-04-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181028033628/https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2016/02/25/sci-hub-how-does-it-work/ |archive-date=2018-10-28 |url-status=live }}</ref>。

截至2014年年底，[[创世纪图书馆|创世纪图书馆]]一直為Sci-Hub的學術資源提供儲存空間。用戶在Sci-Hub上要求的論文會先從創世紀圖書館那邊尋找。若圖書館儲存了其目標資源，則從那裏提供。若沒有，Sci-Hub會以其他方式獲取論文，然後儲存到创世纪图书馆<ref name="eLife" />。Sci-Hub在此之前一直沿用經过6小时就删除缓存内容的系统，故此改用此一永久儲存服務就能讓它為更多用戶提供服務<ref name=Elbakyan2017/>。

自2015年起，Sci-Hub改用自身的伺服器去永久儲存論文<ref name="eLife" /><ref name=Elbakyan2017/>。截至2017年，Sci-Hub仍繼續把[[電子書|電子書]]的請求重新導向至创世纪图书馆<ref name="eLife" /><ref name=Elbakyan2017/>。

2021年，由於該網站所面對的法律挑戰增多，故活動家於[[Reddit|Reddit]]發起了Sci-Hub文章的做種備份計劃，以望利用[[BitTorrent_(协议)|BitTorrent]]技術把Sci-Hub的內容去中心化地儲存和傳送給其他用戶<ref>{{cite news |title=Archivists Want to Make Sci-Hub 'Un-Censorable' |url=https://gizmodo.com/archivists-want-to-make-sci-hub-un-censorable-1846898276 |access-date=2021-06-13 |work=Gizmodo |language=en-us |archive-date=2021-12-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211218112332/https://gizmodo.com/archivists-want-to-make-sci-hub-un-censorable-1846898276 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 使用狀況 ===
[[File:Sci-hub_downloads.png|thumb]]
在sci-hub.org域名被封鎖之前，它日均處理約80,000宗請求<ref name="BohannonBio"/>。它的處理量後來出現上升趨勢——2016年2月，該網站稱自己日均處理200,000宗請求<ref name="Bohannon" />。

2016年，艾爾巴金把2015年9月至2016年2月的伺服器日志數據公開{{Efn|由於期間更換過域名的關係，故丢失了2015年11月的部分數據。|name=Logdatanote}}。根據該些數據，它的用户很多都来自歐美大學的校舍。雖然在考慮人口比例的情況下，[[已開發國家|已開發國家]]的用戶群規模不少，但於[[发展中国家|发展中国家]]發起的下載請求亦佔了一大比例——它們來自伊朗、中国大陸、印度、俄罗斯、巴西、埃及等地。用戶的需求涵蓋不同[[科学分支|科学分支]]<ref name="Bohannon" />。

2017年3月，該網站收錄了6,200萬篇論文<ref name="greshake">{{Cite journal|last=Greshake|first=Bastian|date=2017-04-21|title=Looking into Pandora's Box: The Content ofSci-Hub and its Usage|journal=F1000Research|volume=6|pages=541|doi=10.12688/f1000research.11366.1|issn=2046-1402|pmc=5428489|pmid=28529712}}</ref>。一篇研究指出，當中85%於付費期刊上發表<ref name="eLife"/>。2017年3月，儘管它只收錄了整體已發表文章的69%，但研究者根據2015年至2017年7月的學術文章引-{}-用情況作估計，最後得出「至少96%付費文章的下載請求能夠成功」的結論<ref name="eLife" />。

一篇於2019年發表的研究分析了2,780萬宗Sci-Hub下載記錄，結果顯示當中有2,320万宗是期刊文章請求，470万宗（22%）指向醫學期刊上的文章。中度和低度收入國家佔據了大多數（69%）醫學文獻請求；以絕對數量來計，該些請求大多來自印度、中国大陸、美国、巴西、伊朗<ref>{{cite journal |journal= Lancet Glob Health |date= January 2019 |volume=7 |issue=1|pages=e30–e31| doi= 10.1016/S2214-109X(18)30388-7 |title=Who is pirating medical literature? A bibliometric review of 28 million Sci-Hub downloads |vauthors=Till BM, Rudolfson N, Saluja S, Gnanaraj J, Samad L, Ljungman D, Shrime M|pmid= 30554757 |doi-access=free }}</ref>。

2020年7月27日，Sci-Hub公佈它已累計處理了超過10億宗下載請求，日均有30萬至60萬次下載。它亦表示，自身計劃收錄更多數碼化時代之前的文獻。Sci-Hub亦把收錄「[[查尔斯·达尔文|查尔斯·达尔文]]約15,000封信件」列為2019年取得的重要成就。它們雖在約100年前便不受版權保護，但人們仍不能免費獲得大部分信件。Sci-Hub还表示，營運者將為它开发免费搜索引擎，以讓人們能对数据库中的PDF全文进行关键词搜索。艾爾巴金还計劃於网站上提供期刊文章的补充信息<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vk.com/wall-36928352_39093|title=Все подводят итоги года, а чем Sci-Hub хуже?.. {{!}} Sci-Hub {{!}} Открытый доступ к научной информации|website=vk.com|access-date=2021-06-23|archive-date=2021-06-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210620072903/https://vk.com/wall-36928352_39093|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2019年，幾間圖書館決定取消訂閱付費期刊。部分研究者因此寫道，Sci-Hub減少了付費訂閱對圖書館員的吸引力<ref>{{cite journal|first1=Andrés|last1=Fernández-Ramos|first2=María Blanca|last2=Rodríguez Bravo|first3=María Luisa|last3=Alvite Díez|first4=Lourdes|last4=Santos de Paz|title=Evolution of the big deals use in the public universities of the Castile and Leon region, Spain = Evolución del uso de los big deals en las universidades públicas de Castilla y León|url=https://buleria.unileon.es/handle/10612/11498|journal=El Profesional de la Información|date=2019|volume=28|issue=6|doi=10.3145/epi.2019.nov.19|first5=María Antonia|last5=Morán Suárez|first6=Josefa|last6=Gallego Lorenzo|first7=Isabel|last7=Olea Merino|language=es|doi-access=free|access-date=2021-06-23|archive-date=2020-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927145344/https://buleria.unileon.es/handle/10612/11498|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2020年，一项研究发现，能夠在Sci-Hub下載的文章比不能下載的引-{}-用率高1.72倍<ref>{{cite arxiv|last1=Correa|first1=J. C.|last2=Laverde-Rojas|first2=H.|last3=Marmolejo-Ramos|first3=F.|last4=Tejada|first4=J.|last5=Bahník|first5=Š|date=2020-06-29|title=The Sci-hub Effect: Sci-hub downloads lead to more article citations|class=cs.DL|eprint=2006.14979}}</ref>。學術出版協會的菲尔·戴维斯（Phil Davis）其後質疑它的方法和結論<ref>{{cite web |last1=Davis |first1=Phil |title=Sci-Hub Citation Study Confuses Causes With Effects |url=https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2021/02/08/sci-hub-citation-study-confuses-causes-with-effects/ |website=The Scholarly Kitchen |date=2021-02-08 |access-date=2021-06-23 |archive-date=2021-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211106090505/https://scholarlykitchen.sspnet.org/2021/02/08/sci-hub-citation-study-confuses-causes-with-effects/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
==== 科學研究存檔====
Sci-Hub因為突破了當代版權法的框架，故能有效地為學術出版物存檔。此外它亦不像其他網絡檔案館般，只收錄以開放取用授權的出版物<ref name="Claburn 2020">{{cite web |last1=Claburn |first1=Thomas |title=Open access journals are vanishing from the web, Internet Archive stands ready to fill in the gaps |url=https://www.theregister.com/2020/09/10/open_access_journal/ |website=[[The_Register|The Register]] |language=en |date=2020-09-10 |access-date=2021-06-23 |archive-date=2021-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211029191612/https://www.theregister.com/2020/09/10/open_access_journal/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。Sci-Hub轉儲了不少學術論文<ref name="eLife"/><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Greshake |first1=Bastian |title=Looking into Pandora's Box: The Content of Sci-Hub and its Usage |journal=F1000Research |date=2017 |volume=6 |pages=541 |doi=10.12688/f1000research.11366.1 |pmid=28529712 |pmc=5428489 |issn=2046-1402}}</ref>。

一些活動家為回-{}-應[[2019冠状病毒病疫情|2019冠状病毒病疫情]]，而在Sci-Hub創建超過5,000份有關[[冠状病毒|冠状病毒]]的文章存檔。他們承認此一舉動雖然違法，但卻認為它符合道德義務<ref name="Bender 2020">{{cite web | last=Bender | first=Maddie | title='It's a Moral Imperative:' Archivists Made a Directory of 5,000 Coronavirus Studies to Bypass Paywalls | website=[[Vice_(magazine)|Vice]] | date=2020-02-03 | url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/z3b3v5/archivists-are-bypassing-paywalls-to-share-studies-about-coronaviruses | access-date=2020-02-27 | archive-date=2020-02-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200204162829/https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/z3b3v5/archivists-are-bypassing-paywalls-to-share-studies-about-coronaviruses | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 各地法律 ==
