2021年1月8日，[[Twitter|Twitter]]以Sci-Hub違反防偽政策為由封鎖其賬戶<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2021/1/8/22220738/twitter-sci-hub-suspended-indian-court-case|title=Twitter suspends Sci-Hub account amid Indian court case|first=Kait|last=Sanchez|date=2021-01-08|website=The Verge|access-date=2021-06-23|archive-date=2021-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211029192238/https://www.theverge.com/2021/1/8/22220738/twitter-sci-hub-suspended-indian-court-case|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://telanganatoday.com/twitter-suspends-sci-hub-account-amid-court-case-in-delhi|title=Twitter suspends Sci-Hub account amid court case in Delhi|website=Telangana Today|date=2021-01-09|access-date=2021-06-23|archive-date=2021-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211029124450/https://telanganatoday.com/twitter-suspends-sci-hub-account-amid-court-case-in-delhi|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/sci-hub-founder-criticises-sudden-twitter-ban-over-over-counterfeit-content-210108/|title=Sci-Hub Founder Criticises Sudden Twitter Ban Over Over "Counterfeit" Content * TorrentFreak|access-date=2021-11-05|archive-date=2021-12-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211218090433/https://torrentfreak.com/sci-hub-founder-criticises-sudden-twitter-ban-over-over-counterfeit-content-210108/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 美國 ===
2015年，[[愛思唯爾|愛思唯爾]]在[[美国纽约南区联邦地区法院|美国纽约南区联邦地区法院]]向Sci-Hub提出侵權訴訟<ref name="Schiermeier2017">{{Cite journal|last=Schiermeier|first=Quirin|title=US court grants Elsevier millions in damages from Sci-Hub|url=http://www.nature.com/news/us-court-grants-elsevier-millions-in-damages-from-sci-hub-1.22196|journal= Nature |language=en|doi=10.1038/nature.2017.22196| year=2017|access-date=2017-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170622200235/http://www.nature.com/news/us-court-grants-elsevier-millions-in-damages-from-sci-hub-1.22196|archive-date=2017-06-22|url-status=live}}</ref>。另外分別註冊在荷蘭<ref name=":0" />與俄羅斯<ref>{{Cite news |first = Henry |last = Mance |title = Publishers win landmark case against ebook pirates |url = http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/988850e0-038c-11e5-a70f-00144feabdc0.html |newspaper = [[金融时报_(英国)|Financial Times]] |issn = 0307-1766 |publisher = [[日本經濟新聞|The Nikkei]] |date = 2015-05-26 |access-date = 2015-10-05 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150708065407/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/988850e0-038c-11e5-a70f-00144feabdc0.html |archive-date = 2015-07-08 |url-status=live }}{{paywall}}</ref>兩地的[[创世纪图书馆|创世纪图书馆]]亦於這起訴訟中一同被告<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |title= Academic Publishing Giant Fights to Keep Science Paywalled |url= http://www.gizmodo.com.au/2015/06/academic-publishing-giant-fights-to-keep-science-paywalled/ |work= Gizmodo |publisher= Gawker Media |access-date= 2015-10-05 |first= Maddie |last= Stone |date= 2015-06-15 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151006170125/http://www.gizmodo.com.au/2015/06/academic-publishing-giant-fights-to-keep-science-paywalled/ |archive-date= 2015-10-06 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title= Elsevier acts against research article pirate sites and claims irreparable harm |url= https://theconversation.com/elsevier-acts-against-research-article-pirate-sites-and-claims-irreparable-harm-43293 |date= 2015-06-15 |work= The Conversation |publisher= The Conversation Trust |access-date= 2015-10-05 |first= David |last= Glance |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151006181704/https://theconversation.com/elsevier-acts-against-research-article-pirate-sites-and-claims-irreparable-harm-43293 |archive-date= 2015-10-06 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=":4"/>。它成了當時世上牽涉規模最廣的侵權訴訟案<ref name=Greco2017>{{cite journal |last1=Greco |first1=Albert N. |title=The Kirtsaeng and SCI-HUB Cases: The Major U.S. Copyright Cases in the Twenty-First Century |journal=Publishing Research Quarterly |date=2017-06-08 |volume=33 |issue=3 |pages=238–253 |doi=10.1007/s12109-017-9522-7|s2cid=148777672 }}</ref>。愛思唯爾指控Sci-Hub違反及誘使他人違反《版權法》和《{{link-en|電腦詐欺及濫用法案|Computer Fraud and Abuse Act}}》<ref name=Greco2017/>，要求Sci-Hub賠償損失。並申請[[禁制令|禁制令]]，禁止它再把論文分享出去<ref name=Greco2017/>。

艾爾巴金則反過來指責愛思唯爾，認為它在侵犯《[[世界人權宣言|世界人權宣言]]》第二十七條所提及的科学和文化权：「人人有權自由參加社會之文化生活，欣賞藝術，並共享科學進步及其利益。」<ref name=":5" />她亦向該法院寫信，解釋自己創辦Sci-Hub的原因：「研究者每次做研究時需讀上几十至几百篇论文，它現在說一篇要價32美元。這實在是太瘋狂了」<ref name="torrentfreak.com" />。

Sci-Hub的伺服器位於俄羅斯[[圣彼得堡|圣彼得堡]]，美國法院所下的任何判決皆對之沒有約束力<ref name=":0" />。它當時亦不派人出庭答辯<ref name="Schiermeier2017"/>。2017年6月，法院在答辯人缺席的情況下，宣判Sci-Hub等需向愛思唯爾賠償1500萬美元<ref name="Schiermeier2017"/>。判决书寫道，Sci-Hub利用學生及學術機構的[[ScienceDirect|ScienceDirect]]帳戶，獲取由愛思唯爾出版的論文<ref name=":0" />。此外愛思唯爾亦成功申請禁制令，令Sci-Hub失去原域名sci-hub.org<ref name="eLife" /><ref name=shadowill/><ref name="independent">{{cite web|last1=Henderson|first1=Emma|title=Pirate website offering millions of academic papers for free refuses to close despite lawsuit|date=2016-02-15|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/pirate-website-offering-millions-of-academic-papers-for-free-refuses-to-close-despite-law-suit-a6875001.html|work=The Independent| publisher=Independent Print Limited|access-date=2016-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160217205512/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/pirate-website-offering-millions-of-academic-papers-for-free-refuses-to-close-despite-law-suit-a6875001.html| archive-date=2016-02-17|url-status=live}}</ref>。

2017年6月，[[美国化学学会|美国化学学会]]在當地[[美国弗吉尼亚东区联邦地区法院|弗吉尼亚东区联邦地区法院]]向Sci-Hub提出侵權訴訟，要求它賠償480万美元的損失，並認為互聯網服務供應商應封鎖Sci-Hub<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.insidehighered.com/quicktakes/2017/09/06/american-chemical-society-moves-block-access-sci-hub|title=American Chemical Society Moves to Block Access to Sci-Hub|work=Inside Higher Ed|first=Lindsay|last=McKenzie|date=2017-09-06|access-date=2017-09-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906195809/https://www.insidehighered.com/quicktakes/2017/09/06/american-chemical-society-moves-block-access-sci-hub|archive-date=2017-09-06|url-status=live}}</ref>。2017年11月6日，學會在答辯人缺席的情況下勝訴，成功申請禁令，禁止「互联网搜索引擎、网络托管和互联网服务提供商、域名注册商和域名注册機構」在服務上为访问Sci-Hub提供便利<ref name=Chawla>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/11/court-demands-search-engines-and-internet-service-providers-block-sci-hub|title=Court demands that search engines and internet service providers block Sci-Hub|work=Science {{!}} AAAS|first=Dalmeet Singh|last=Chawla| date=2017-11-06|language=en|access-date=2017-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171123071628/http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/11/court-demands-search-engines-and-internet-service-providers-block-sci-hub|archive-date=2017-11-23|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=EFF2017>{{Cite web |url=https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2017/11/another-court-overreaches-site-blocking-order-targeting-sci-hub |title=Another Court Overreaches With Site-Blocking Order Targeting Sci-Hub |last=Stoltz |first=Mitch |date=2017-11-10 |website=Electronic Frontier Foundation |language=en |access-date=2018-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181207180328/https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2017/11/another-court-overreaches-site-blocking-order-targeting-sci-hub |archive-date=2018-12-07 |url-status=live }}</ref>。同月23日，4個Sci-Hub域名因法庭命令而變得不活躍<ref>{{cite news |last1=Silver |first1=Andrew |title=Sci-Hub domains inactive following court order |url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2017/11/23/sci_hubs_become_inactive_following_court_order/ |work=The Register |date=2017-11-23 |language=en |access-date=2018-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181017123635/https://www.theregister.co.uk/2017/11/23/sci_hubs_become_inactive_following_court_order/ |archive-date=2018-10-17 |url-status=live }}</ref>，[[Cloudflare|Cloudflare]]亦終止Sci-Hub的帳戶<ref name=Scientist2018>{{cite news |last1=Kwon |first1=Diana |title=Sci-Hub Loses Domains and Access to Some Web Services |url=https://www.the-scientist.com/daily-news/sci-hub-loses-domains-and-access-to-some-web-services-30264 |work=The Scientist Magazine |date=2018-02-20 |language=en |access-date=2018-10-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181122145223/https://www.the-scientist.com/daily-news/sci-hub-loses-domains-and-access-to-some-web-services-30264 |archive-date=2018-11-22 |url-status=live }}</ref>。

白宮[[美國貿易代表處|美國貿易代表處]]於2018年和2019年兩度把Sci-Hub視為最明目張膽的「[[惡名市場|惡名市場]]」<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://ustr.gov/sites/default/files/2018_Notorious_Markets_List.pdf| title=USTR| access-date=2021-06-23| archive-date=2020-08-02| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200802053610/https://ustr.gov/sites/default/files/2018_Notorious_Markets_List.pdf| dead-url=no}}</ref>。

《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》在2019年12月報導指，美國司法部正在調查艾爾巴金是否跟俄羅斯情報部門有關。他們認為Sci-Hub需得到俄罗斯政府的默许或协助，才能發展成這麼大規模的影子圖書館<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/justice-department-investigates-sci-hub-founder-on-suspicion-of-working-for-russian-intelligence/2019/12/19/9dbcb6e6-2277-11ea-a153-dce4b94e4249_story.html|title=Justice Department Investigates Sci-Hub Founder on Suspicion of Working For Russian Intelligence|work=[[华盛顿邮报|The Washington Post]]|date=2019-12-19|access-date=2021-11-05|archive-date=2020-09-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200909152259/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/justice-department-investigates-sci-hub-founder-on-suspicion-of-working-for-russian-intelligence/2019/12/19/9dbcb6e6-2277-11ea-a153-dce4b94e4249_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。愛思唯爾亦指責Sci-Hub會構成安全隱患，藉此鼓勵各教育機構封鎖之<ref>{{Cite web|title=Universities ignore growing concern over Sci-Hub cyber risk|url=https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2020/01/17/universities-ignore-growing-concern-over-sci-hub-cyber-risk|access-date=2021-08-03|website=www.insidehighered.com|language=en|archive-date=2021-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211029170756/https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2020/01/17/universities-ignore-growing-concern-over-sci-hub-cyber-risk|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Okere, K 2021">Okere, K. and G. Evans (2021). "A Librarian’s Perspective on Sci-Hub’s Impact on Users and the Library." Serials Librarian</ref>。

