愛思唯爾、[[施普林格科学+商业媒体|施普林格]]、[[約翰威立|約翰威立]]、[[劍橋大學出版社|劍橋大學出版社]]已在比利時法院中勝訴，令當地互聯網服務供應商須封鎖Sci-Hub和創世紀圖書館。它們在訴訟中指出，該些網站9成以上學術文獻都屬於盗版<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lecho.be/entreprises/technologie/les-editeurs-scientifiques-se-liguent-contre-la-piraterie/10172391.html|title=Les éditeurs scientifiques se liguent contre la piraterie|date=2019-10-16|website=L'Echo|language=fr|access-date=2020-01-14|archive-date=2021-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210513183744/https://www.lecho.be/entreprises/technologie/les-editeurs-scientifiques-se-liguent-contre-la-piraterie/10172391.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 印度 ===
2020年12月，愛思唯爾、約翰威立、[[美国化学学会|美国化学学会]]在[[德里高等法院|德里高等法院]]提出訴訟，控告Sci-Hub和創世紀圖書館侵犯版權。它們亦要求法院頒佈動態禁令，以讓Sci-Hub即使在將來更換域名或IP地址，也會受到禁令影響<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sci-Hub & Libgen Face ISP Blocking in India After Publishers File High Court Complaint|website=TorrentFreak|last=Maxwell|first=Andy|url=https://torrentfreak.com/sci-hub-libgen-face-isp-blocking-in-india-after-publishers-file-high-court-complaint-201227/|access-date=2021-05-13|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201227193825/https://torrentfreak.com/sci-hub-libgen-face-isp-blocking-in-india-after-publishers-file-high-court-complaint-201227/|archive-date=2020-12-27}}</ref>。 高等法院於是頒佈臨時禁令，限制這些網站在2021年1月6日前上傳、發表、提供任何文章<ref>{{cite news |last1=Banka |first1=Richa |title=Delhi HC asks Libgen, Sci-Hub to stop uploading articles as they face copyright infringement charges |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/delhi-hc-asks-libgen-sci-hub-to-stop-uploading-articles-as-they-face-copyright-infringement-charges/story-cRWCB1sGs1yMqR3TCpuvmL.html |access-date=2020-12-24 |work=[[印度斯坦时报|Hindustan Times]]|date=2020-12-24|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201227014904/https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/delhi-hc-asks-libgen-sci-hub-to-stop-uploading-articles-as-they-face-copyright-infringement-charges/story-cRWCB1sGs1yMqR3TCpuvmL.html|archive-date=2020-12-27}}</ref>。「r/DataHoarder」板塊上的Reddit用戶為了回應這起訴訟，而發起Sci-Hub文章的做種備份計劃，以望有關內容能夠不受審查地去中心化<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sg.style.yahoo.com/fans-sci-hub-mobilizing-save-132414822.html|last=Barre|first=Axel|title=Fans of Sci-Hub are mobilizing to save the pirate science platform|website=[[雅虎|Yahoo! Lifestyle]]|date=2021-05-20|access-date=2021-05-24|url-status=live|language=en|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210525020045/https://sg.style.yahoo.com/fans-sci-hub-mobilizing-save-132414822.html|archive-date=2021-05-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Activists Mobilize to Fight Censorship and Save Open Science|url=https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2021/05/activists-mobilize-fight-censorship-and-save-open-science|website=[[电子前哨基金会|Electronic Frontier Foundation]]|date=2021-05-24|last=Mir|first=Rory|access-date=2021-05-24|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210525003033/https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2021/05/activists-mobilize-fight-censorship-and-save-open-science|archive-date=2021-05-25}}</ref>。

2021年1月6日，高等法院決定在聽取科學家、研究者、學生的陳詞之前，不下達任何命令<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-01-07|title=SCI hub, Libgen case: Delhi HC to hear students, researchers|last=Banka|first=Richa|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/sci-hub-libgen-case-delhi-hc-to-hear-students-researchers/story-PxBftjgAPFPfuXGok4qG7N.html|access-date=2021-04-14|website=[[印度斯坦时报|Hindustan Times]]|language=en|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210107184949/https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/sci-hub-libgen-case-delhi-hc-to-hear-students-researchers/story-PxBftjgAPFPfuXGok4qG7N.html|archive-date=2021-01-07|url-status=live}}</ref>。12月16日，高等法院舉辦了一場聽證會<ref name=":10">{{Cite journal|last=Else|first=Holly|date=2021-12-13|title=What Sci-Hub’s latest court battle means for research|url=https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-021-03659-0|journal=Nature|language=en|volume=600|issue=7889|pages=370–371|doi=10.1038/d41586-021-03659-0|access-date=2021-12-22|archive-date=2021-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211222191228/https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-021-03659-0|dead-url=no}}</ref>。根據印度版權法的[[公平處理|公平處理]]條款，教學過程中所使用的材料能夠獲得版權豁免。而Sci-Hub亦為「當地研究者提供教育資源」，因此辯護者認為有關條款適用於此案。當地法院曾以該條款裁定「教育機構為低收入學生提供教材的複印本」為合法行為<ref name=":10"/>。不少印度學者站在Sci-Hub的一方，紛紛提交聲援該網站的請願書。{{link-en|梁日明|Lawrence Liang}}亦為該網站爭取科學界支-{}-持<ref name=":10"/>。

=== 英國 ===
2021年2月，愛思唯爾和施普林格·自然成功向英國法院申請禁令，要求當地電訊商TalkTalk封鎖sci-hub.se<ref>{{Cite web|last=Maxwell|first=Andy|date=2021-02-18|title=Sci-Hub: Elsevier and Springer Nature Obtain UK ISP Blocking Order * TorrentFreak|url=https://torrentfreak.com/sci-hub-elsevier-and-springer-nature-obtain-uk-isp-blocking-order-210218/|access-date=2021-02-19|language=en|archive-date=2021-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210927205216/https://torrentfreak.com/sci-hub-elsevier-and-springer-nature-obtain-uk-isp-blocking-order-210218/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2021年3月，伦敦警察局知识产权罪案调查队向学生和大学发出警告，反对任何人访问该网站，并要求大学封锁之。它同時指控该网站可能會為了從出版商下載文獻，而窃取凭证，用戶亦可能會在「无意中下载潜在有害内容」<ref>{{Cite news|date=2021-03-19|title=Police warn students to avoid science website|language=en-GB|work=BBC News|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/education-56462390|access-date=2021-03-20|archive-date=2021-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211124184711/https://www.bbc.com/news/education-56462390|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Police warn students and universities of accessing an illegal website to download published scientific papers|url=https://colp.mpw.cds.co.uk/news/city-of-london/news/2021/march/police-warn-students-and-universities-of-accessing-an-illegal-website-to-download-published-scientific-papers/|access-date=2021-03-20|website=colp.mpw.cds.co.uk|language=en-gb|archive-date=2021-10-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211024172805/https://colp.mpw.cds.co.uk/news/city-of-london/news/2021/march/police-warn-students-and-universities-of-accessing-an-illegal-website-to-download-published-scientific-papers/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。艾爾巴金否認上述指控<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sci-Hub: Police warn students and universities against using 'the Pirate Bay of science'|url=https://news.sky.com/story/police-warn-students-and-universities-against-using-the-pirate-bay-of-science-12250407|access-date=2021-03-20|website=Sky News|language=en|archive-date=2021-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211109083318/https://news.sky.com/story/police-warn-students-and-universities-against-using-the-pirate-bay-of-science-12250407|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==迴響==
[[File:Alexandra_Elbakyan.jpg|thumb]]

與典型付費訂閱網站相比，用戶普遍較喜歡Sci-Hub的界面，認為它能提供較好的體驗，而且用起來十分方便<ref name=shadowill/>。

部分評論家認為Sci-Hub改變了「我們獲得知識的途徑」<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bigthink.com/natalie-shoemaker/sci-hub-has-changed-how-we-access-knowledge|title=Which countries are accessing Sci-Hub, created by Alexandra Elbakyan?|last=Shoemaker|first=Natalie|date=2016-05-03|website=Big Think|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828141853/http://bigthink.com/natalie-shoemaker/sci-hub-has-changed-how-we-access-knowledge|archive-date=2016-08-28|url-status=live}}</ref>。它也讓人們開始意識及反思科學出版界的商業模式——讓研究機構付費取回自己發表的文章，同時要人無償提供和審閱文章<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2011/aug/29/academic-publishers-murdoch-socialist|title=Academic publishers make Murdoch look like a socialist {{!}} George Monbiot|last=Monbiot|first=George|date=2011-08-29|work=the Guardian|access-date=2019-03-10|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190307174619/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2011/aug/29/academic-publishers-murdoch-socialist|archive-date=2019-03-07|url-status=live}}</ref>。

科學出版物的[[开放获取|开放获取]]支-{}-持者則把開放取用的範圍再度擴展——科學歐洲於2018年9月4日發起[[Plan_S|Plan S]]倡议<ref>{{cite news |title=Coalition of European Funders Announces "Plan S" to Require Full OA, Cap APCs, & Disallow Publication in Hybrid Journals |url=https://sparcopen.org/news/2018/coalition-european-funders-announces-plan-s/ |work=SPARC |date=2018-09-04 |accessdate=2021-12-23 |archive-date=2019-01-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190116100408/https://sparcopen.org/news/2018/coalition-european-funders-announces-plan-s/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Plan S: Accelerating the transition to full and immediate Open Access to scientific publications |url=https://www.scienceeurope.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Plan_S.pdf |website=<!-- 沒有連結 -->[[Science_Europe|Science Europe]] |access-date=2018-09-13 |date=2018-09-04 |archive-date=2018-09-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180904122211/https://www.scienceeurope.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Plan_S.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。它最初稱為「cOAlition S」<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scienceeurope.org/coalition-s/|title=Science Europe – cOAlition S|website=www.scienceeurope.org|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-09-15|archive-date=2018-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181005074754/https://www.scienceeurope.org/coalition-s/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此一計劃由歐洲研究委員會和12個歐洲國家的國家級研究機構和資助者發起，並要求2020年起，受益於國家資助的科學家和研究人員必須將所有研究成果發表在开放获取的资料库或期刊上<ref name="Economist">{{cite news |title=European countries demand that publicly funded research should be free to all |url=https://www.economist.com/science-and-technology/2018/09/15/european-countries-demand-that-publicly-funded-research-should-be-free-to-all |work=[[经济学人|The Economist]] |date=2018-09-15 |access-date=2018-09-13 |archive-date=2021-10-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211002110323/https://www.economist.com/science-and-technology/2018/09/15/european-countries-demand-that-publicly-funded-research-be-free |dead-url=no }}</ref>。不過它並非一項硬性的法規<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2016/may/28/eu-ministers-2020-target-free-access-scientific-papers|title=All scientific papers to be free by 2020 under EU proposals|last=Khomami|first=Nadia|date=2016-05-28|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-03-10|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190311212159/https://www.theguardian.com/science/2016/may/28/eu-ministers-2020-target-free-access-scientific-papers|archive-date=2019-03-11|url-status=live}}</ref>。

一些歐洲國家的科學家開始跟愛思唯爾等學術出版社協商，以望科學出版物能夠於全國开放获取<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/10/german-researchers-resign-elsevier-journals-push-nationwide-open-access|title=German researchers resign from Elsevier journals in push for nationwide open access|last1=VogelOct. 13|first1=Gretchen|last2=2017|date=2017-10-13|website=Science {{!}} AAAS|language=en|access-date=2019-03-15|last3=Pm|first3=3:30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322172128/https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/10/german-researchers-resign-elsevier-journals-push-nationwide-open-access|archive-date=2019-03-22|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.enago.com/academy/move-boycott-elsevier-journals-deal-near-dead/|title=Elsevier's Open Access Controversy: German Researchers Resign to Register Protest|date=2017-10-19|website=Enago Academy|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606095631/https://www.enago.com/academy/move-boycott-elsevier-journals-deal-near-dead/|archive-date=2019-06-06|url-status=live}}</ref>。

出版商對Sci-Hub有着不少批評，甚至称它正在破坏更為人接受的开放获取倡议<ref name="ALM">{{Cite web|last=Banks|first=Marcus|url=https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|title=Sci-Hub: What It Is and Why It Matters|date=2016-05-31|website=American Libraries|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918042400/https://americanlibrariesmagazine.org/2016/05/31/why-sci-hub-matters/|archive-date=2016-09-18|url-status=live}}</ref>。同時表示它忽略了出版商為讓第三世界的人民獲得知識，而作的努力<ref name="ALM" />。圖書館員亦批評它危害大學的[[网络安全|网络安全]]和教職員獲得合法論文的途徑<ref name="Ruff" /><ref name="ALM" /><ref name="RussellSanchez" /><ref name="SK" />。反駁者則認為大型出版商為保自身利益而誇大有關网络安全威胁<ref name="timeshighereducation.com"/>。然而，即使是[[哈佛大学|哈佛大学]]和[[康奈尔大学|康奈尔大学]]，也因為訂閱成本上漲而取消訂閱出版商的期刊<ref>{{Cite web|website=sciencealert.com|url=http://www.sciencealert.com/this-woman-has-illegally-uploaded-millions-of-journal-articles-in-an-attempt-to-open-up-science|title=Researcher illegally shares millions of science papers free online to spread knowledge|date=2016-02-12|last=MacDonald|first=Fiona|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821054849/http://www.sciencealert.com/this-woman-has-illegally-uploaded-millions-of-journal-articles-in-an-attempt-to-open-up-science|archive-date=2016-08-21|url-status=live}}</ref>，这可能令美國知名學府的所在城市更熱於使用Sci-Hub（但背後原因可能並非無法獲得論文，而是用起來較方便）<ref name=Bohannon/>。Sci-Hub的出現亦被視為大勢所趨，符合人們愈來愈容易獲得研究成果的趨勢<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasas-making-it-easier-check-out-research-its-funding-180960172/?no-ist|title=Soon Everyone Will Be Able to Read NASA-Funded Research|date=2016-08-22|last=Lewis|first=Danny|website=smithsonian.com|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825073336/http://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasas-making-it-easier-check-out-research-its-funding-180960172/?no-ist|archive-date=2016-08-25|url-status=live}}</ref>。很多學術研究者、大學圖書館員、开放获取支持者相信，艾爾巴金「為學術出版界帶來了[[Napster|Napster]]」般的事物，意指Sci-Hub「會永久改變整個行業生態」<ref name=WaPo/>。艾爾巴金亦因創立Sci-Hub，而被捧為「英雄」或「[[亚伦·斯沃茨|亚伦·斯沃茨]]的繼承者」。後者在2010年透過[[JSTOR|JSTOR]]下載数以百万计的学术文章<ref name=":4" /><ref name=":6">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/13/opinion/sunday/should-all-research-papers-be-free.html|title=Should All Research Papers Be Free?|last=Murphy|first=Kate|date=2016-03-12|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031030302/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/13/opinion/sunday/should-all-research-papers-be-free.html|archive-date=2016-10-31|url-status=live}}</ref>。此外亦有人把她跟[[爱德华·斯诺登|爱德华·斯诺登]]相提並論<ref name=":6" />。她還獲得當代「[[罗宾汉|罗宾汉]]」或「科學界罗宾汉」的讚稱<ref name="bigthink">{{cite news|url=http://bigthink.com/neurobonkers/a-pirate-bay-for-science|title=Meet the Robin Hood of Science|last=Oxenham|first=Simon|date=2016-02-10|access-date=2016-02-22|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160217155028/http://bigthink.com/neurobonkers/a-pirate-bay-for-science|archive-date=2016-02-17|publisher=The Big Think, Inc.}}</ref>。

[[加利福尼亞州立大學|加利福尼亞州立大學]]研究者加布里埃尔·J.加德纳（Gabriel J. Gardner）曾研究過Sci-Hub及其他同類網站，並就此於[[美國圖書館協會|美國圖書館協會]]的聚會上發表意見。2016年8月，{{link-en|美國出版商協會|Association of American Publishers}}向他寄了一封信，於當中要求他不要再推廣Sci-Hub<ref>{{cite news |last1=Peet |first1=Lisa |title=Sci-Hub Controversy Triggers Publishers' Critique of Librarian |url=https://www.libraryjournal.com/?detailStory=sci-hub-controversy-triggers-publishers-critique-of-librarian |work=The Library Journal |date=2016-08-25 |access-date=2018-12-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181013211828/https://www.libraryjournal.com/?detailStory=sci-hub-controversy-triggers-publishers-critique-of-librarian |archive-date=2018-10-13 |url-status=live }}</ref>。出版商協會因此受到不少批評，認為它在打壓一項合法研究。該一信件隨後公諸於世，並得到[[加州州立大学长滩分校|加州州立大学长滩分校]]图书馆服务主任的回-{}-應。他在回-{}-應中聲援加德纳<ref>{{cite web|last= Jaschik|first= Scott|url= https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2016/08/08/letter-publishers-group-adds-debate-over-sci-hub-and-librarians-who-study-it|title= Letter from publishers' group adds to debate over Sci-Hub and librarians who study it|date= 2016-08-08|website= Inside Higher Ed|access-date= 2016-08-29|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160814185208/https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2016/08/08/letter-publishers-group-adds-debate-over-sci-hub-and-librarians-who-study-it|archive-date= 2016-08-14|url-status=live}}</ref>。

2016年12月，《[[自然_(期刊)|自然]]》期刊將亞歷珊卓·艾爾巴金列為2016年度[[自然科學十人|十大科學人物]]之一<ref name=":7"/>。

